The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has reported the deaths of 17 more persons to COVID-19 related complications. The NCDC in its daily update at 11.55pm on Saturday also disclosed that 220 more persons had been confirmed to have contracted the disease. The number of COVID-19 casualties in the country has climbed to 85 and confirmed cases now stand at 2,388. ‪ The latest update saw Lagos taking back the lead from Kano – which was on top in the last two days – with 62 new cases and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), following closely behind with 52 cases. ‪ This is followed by Kaduna, Sokoto and Kebbi States with 31, 13 and 10 states, respectively. ‬ ‪ Yobe State, recorded nine cases, Borno State, six cases, Bauchi and Edo states, five cases each, while Gombe, Enugu and Oyo states recorded four cases each. While ‬Zamfara had three cases, Nasarawa, Osun, Ebonyi, Kwara, Kano and Plateau states recorded two cases each. ‪ ‬ ‪ ‪